doc.after: The exterior of the Royal Albert Hall built in 1867 71 to the designs of Francis Fowke and Henry Young Darracott Scott is embellished with a mosaic frieze composed of sixteen separate designs by multiple artists This was assembled from 800 slabs prepared by attendees of the South Kensington Museum s mosaic class the terracotta was manufactured by Minton Hollins and Company The designs are listed below in anti clockwise order from the north 118
